short tail vs long tail keyword


ğŸ”¹ Short-Tail Keywords

    1 to 2 words

    Very broad and general

    High search volume

    High competition

    Harder to rank

âœ… Example:

    â€œshoesâ€

    â€œlaptopâ€

    â€œpizzaâ€

ğŸ”¸ Intent is not clear â€“ You don't know exactly what the user wants.
ğŸ”¹ Long-Tail Keywords

    3 or more words

    Very specific

    Low search volume (each)

    Low competition

    Easier to rank

    Higher conversion rate (because it matches user intent)

âœ… Example:

    â€œbest running shoes for flat feetâ€

    â€œbuy budget laptop for studentsâ€

    â€œvegan pizza near meâ€

ğŸ”¸ Intent is clear â€“ You know exactly what the user is looking for.
ğŸ“Œ Summary:
Feature	Short-Tail	Long-Tail
Length	1â€“2 words	3+ words
Specificity	General	Very specific
